  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Cardiac Surgery for 4 African Children</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The per capita income in Cameroon is about $1,110; heart surgery costs about $7,000.  Children die of heart disease every day because their families could not afford treatment.  A four-year-old girl named (prophetically, we hope!)  Success has a heart defect that she has been waiting two years to have corrected.  Her parents can only afford doctor visits and medicine to monitor and mitigate her condition.  We hope to be able to fund the surgery she needs -- and to also sponsor 2 more children.</narrative>
  </description>
